# Deployment Rules

References:

- docs/deployment-guide.md
- docs/tech-architecture.md

---

# Purpose

Ensure deployments are:

- Repeatable
- Reliable
- Observable
- Secure

---

# Deployment Strategy

Environment Promotion

Development

↓

Staging

↓

Production

---

Never deploy directly from local machine to production.

---

# Environment Rules

Supported Environments

Development

Staging

Production

---

Environment specific settings must be externalized.

---

Forbidden

```json
{
  "ConnectionString": "Production Database"
}
```

---

Use environment variables.

---

# Configuration Rules

All configurable values must come from:

Environment Variables

Configuration Files

Secret Store

---

Examples

Database Connection String

JWT Secret

Google OAuth Secret

Webhook Secret

Provider Tokens

---

Never hardcode environment values.

---

# Infrastructure

Recommended MVP

Frontend

Vercel

---

Backend

Docker Container

---

Database

PostgreSQL

---

Cache

Redis (Future)

---

Background Jobs

Hangfire

---

# Docker Rules

Backend must support Docker.

Required Files

Dockerfile

.dockerignore

---

Container must be stateless.

---

Do not store:

User Files

Logs

Temporary Data

inside containers.

---

# Database Migration Rules

Use:

EF Core Migrations

---

Never manually modify production schema.

---

Deployment Flow

Deploy

↓

Run Migration

↓

Start Application

---

Migrations must be version controlled.

---

# Health Checks

Required Endpoint

```text
/health
```

---

Must verify

Application

Database

Provider Connectivity (optional)

---

Deployment should fail if health check fails.

---

# CI/CD Rules

Recommended

GitHub Actions

---

Pipeline

Build

↓

Test

↓

Lint

↓

Package

↓

Deploy

---

Production deployment requires:

Successful build

Successful tests

---

# Release Rules

Version Format

```text
v1.0.0
```

Semantic Versioning

---

Major

Breaking Changes

---

Minor

New Features

---

Patch

Bug Fixes

---

# Rollback Rules

Every deployment must support rollback.

---

Rollback should restore:

Application Version

Configuration

---

Database rollback should be carefully planned.

---

# Logging Rules

Environment

Application Version

Deployment Time

must be logged at startup.

---

# Monitoring Rules

Monitor

Application Health

Error Rate

Response Time

Webhook Failures

Background Job Failures

---

# Backup Rules

Database Backups

Daily

---

Retention

Minimum 30 Days

---

Backup restore procedure should be documented.

---

# Production Rules

Production must:

Use HTTPS

Use Secure Secrets

Enable Logging

Enable Monitoring

Enable Health Checks

---

Disable:

Swagger UI (public access)

Detailed Exception Pages

Debug Endpoints

---

# Frontend Deployment

Build Artifacts Only.

---

Do not expose:

API Secrets

Provider Secrets

Environment Secrets

---

Frontend environment variables must be public-safe.

---

# Backend Deployment

Run as non-root user.

---

Expose only required ports.

---

Avoid unnecessary packages in image.

---

# Scaling Rules

MVP

Single Backend Instance

---

Future

Horizontal Scaling

Load Balancer

Redis Cache

Background Workers

---

# Disaster Recovery

Must Document

Backup Procedure

Restore Procedure

Rollback Procedure

---

# Testing Requirements

✓ Docker Build

✓ Migration Execution

✓ Health Check

✓ Environment Variables

✓ Production Configuration

✓ CI Pipeline

✓ Rollback Procedure

---

# Documentation Rules

If deployment changes:

Update

- deployment-guide.md
- tech-architecture.md

---

# Code Generation Checklist

✓ Docker Support

✓ Environment Variables

✓ Health Checks

✓ EF Migrations

✓ CI/CD Ready

✓ Backup Strategy

✓ Monitoring Enabled

✓ Rollback Supported

Deployment reliability is a feature, not an afterthought.
